🔧 Correct Approach: Get Exercise Details by ID
The /exercises/name/ endpoint gives us basic info, but we need to call a different endpoint to get the full exercise details (which includes the GIF URL).
Update Your Code:
javascriptasync searchExerciseGif(exerciseName) {
  try {
    const rapidApiKey = process.env.RAPIDAPI_KEY;
    
    if (!rapidApiKey) {
      return null;
    }

    // Step 1: Search for exercise by name to get ID
    let searchName = exerciseName.toLowerCase().trim()
      .replace(/^dumbbell\s+/i, '')
      .replace(/^barbell\s+/i, '')
      .replace(/^cable\s+/i, '')
      .replace(/^machine\s+/i, '');

    const searchResponse = await axios.get(
      `https://exercisedb.p.rapidapi.com/exercises/name/${encodeURIComponent(searchName)}`,
      {
        headers: {
          'X-RapidAPI-Key': rapidApiKey,
          'X-RapidAPI-Host': 'exercisedb.p.rapidapi.com'
        },
        timeout: 5000
      }
    );

    if (!searchResponse.data || searchResponse.data.length === 0) {
      return null;
    }

    const exerciseId = searchResponse.data[0].id;

    // Step 2: Get full exercise details by ID (includes gifUrl)
    const detailsResponse = await axios.get(
      `https://exercisedb.p.rapidapi.com/exercises/exercise/${exerciseId}`,
      {
        headers: {
          'X-RapidAPI-Key': rapidApiKey,
          'X-RapidAPI-Host': 'exercisedb.p.rapidapi.com'
        },
        timeout: 5000
      }
    );

    if (detailsResponse.data && detailsResponse.data.gifUrl) {
      console.log(`✅ GIF found: ${exerciseName} → ${detailsResponse.data.gifUrl}`);
      return detailsResponse.data.gifUrl;
    }

    return null;

  } catch (error) {
    console.error(`Error searching for ${exerciseName}:`, error.message);
    return null;
  }
}
The key change: We now make 2 API calls:

Search by name → get the exercise ID
Get exercise details by ID → get the actual gifUrl


